<p><span class="catchln" id="sec_12-704i">Sec. 12-704i. Credit for delivery of a fetus born dead for which a fetal death certificate has been filed.</span> A taxpayer shall be allowed a credit against the tax imposed under this chapter, other than the liability imposed by section <a href ="chap_229.htm#sec_12-707">12-707</a>, in the amount of two thousand five hundred dollars for the delivery of a fetus born dead for which a fetal death certificate has been filed, provided such child would have been a dependent on such taxpayer&#x0027;s federal income tax return. The credit shall be allowed for the taxable year for which a fetal death occurred.</p>
<p class="source-first">(P.A. 22-118, S. 412; P.A. 23-31, S. 10.)</p>
